author: FOX News Radio
title: House Rejects Obama-Backed Trade Bill
text:
Jun 12, 2015 (AP Photo/Carolyn Kaster) 
A trade bill pushed by the President has failed in the House, after debate that blurred the lines on Capitol Hill. 
FOX News Radio’s Jon Decker reports from the White House: Audio clip: Listen to audio clip. 
If the President was hoping to change some minds about his trade bill with his visit to House Democrats this morning [Friday], he clearly failed in that effort. 
(Pelosi) “I will be voting today to slow down the fast-track to get a better deal for the American people.” 
House Speaker Nancy Pelosi was among scores of Democrats who defied the President and effectively killed so-called fast-track trade legislation by voting against the Trade Adjustment Assistance bill — a program that retrains workers displaced by trade agreements. 
Under House procedures, TAA had to pass the House for the President’s trade bill to be considered. 
At the White House, Jon Decker, FOX News Radio.
